Package posl.engine.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Collection
    Collects the remaining parameters into the given collection
    Command
    Command is used to identify a method that will be wrapped by a MethodProxy executable
    Namespace
    Namespace provides a subcontext of stateful data that may be passed and used to perform executions
    Optional
    Informs the proxy that this method parameter is optional and can be null
    Primitive
    Used to define a method that will be executed once, the result of that method will be placed as the value for the provided key.
    Property
